    "body": "I think we should keep y = pYthon code for now.  I do think that x/c/v\nmust be cut/copy/paste.  We may need a second prefix, but I think we\nshould wait on that to see what other keyboard shortcuts we end up\nneeding.\n\nOn Fri, Jan 13, 2012 at 10:23 AM, Fernando Perez\nreply@reply.github.com\nwrote:\n\n> We thought it would be even more cruel to have cut/copy/paste _not_ use x/c/v, since those are probably the most widely used shortcuts in the world.  But it's true that we could consider introducing a second prefix... We are going to run out of `C-m` options pretty soon, so perhaps a second group of keybindings would be a good idea.  Worth thinking about and planning for the long term; @ellisonbg, what's your take on this?\n> \n> ---\n> \n> Reply to this email directly or view it on GitHub:\n> https://github.com/ipython/ipython/issues/1263#issuecomment-3483960\n\n## \n\nBrian E. Granger\nCal Poly State University, San Luis Obispo\nbgranger@calpoly.edu and ellisonbg@gmail.com\n"
  },
